Description.
Ocellar triangle dark brown, with ca. 2 or 3 setae above ocellar setae. Frons brownish (
Fig. 6M
). Pedicel brownish yellow; first flagellomere yellowish (
Fig. 6M
). Clypeus entirely brownish. Palpus brownish (
Fig. 6M
). Mesonotum brownish yellow, brownish in front of scutellum (
Fig. 6N
). Postpronotal lobe yellow (
Fig. 6O
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 14–16 irregular rows (
Fig. 6N
). Scutellum entirely dark brown to black (
Fig. 6N
). Pleura with a brownish to brown, longitudinal stripe above (
Fig. 6O
). Katepisternum and mesopleuron mostly yellow (
Fig. 6O
). Wing (
Fig. 3C
): distally clouded; costal vein between R 
2+3
and R 
4+5
distally with ca. 5 or 6 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
4+5
and M 
1
slightly divergent distally; halter mostly yellowish, with a brownish to brown patch at knob (
Fig. 6N
). Abdominal tergites dark brown to black, 2nd tergite yellow medially and laterally, 3rd and 4th tergites anteriorly yellow (
Fig. 10D, E
), 3rd tergite entirely setigerous, sometimes setigerous laterally and only on posterior margin in males (
Fig. 10D
). Male terminalia: Epandrium lacking pubescence, with ca. 16 setae near posterior and ventral margins per side (
Fig. 26A
). Cercus lacking pubescence (
Fig. 26A
). Surstylus pubescent (
Fig. 26A
). Hypandrium with 2 sensilla (
Fig. 26B
). Paramere with ca. 10 sensilla distally (
Fig. 26C
).
